<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf6f3fc8e-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s57520"><num value="57520">§ 57520.</num><heading> Vessel maintenance</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf6f3fc8f-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s57520/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">In General</inline>.—</heading><chapeau>A charter under this chapter shall require the charterer, at the charterer’s expense, to—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf6f3fc90-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s57520/a/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> keep the chartered vessel in good repair and efficient operating condition; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf6f3fc91-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s57520/a/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> make any repairs required by the Secretary of Transportation.</content>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf6f3fc92-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s57520/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Inspection</inline>.—</heading><content>The charter shall provide that the Secretary has the right to inspect the vessel at any time to ascertain its condition.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idf6f3fc93-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/109/304/s8/c">Pub. L. 109–304, § 8(c)</ref>, <date date="2006-10-06">Oct. 6, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/1668">120 Stat. 1668</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
